# ⚽ FIFA World Cup 2026 Performance Analysis

> An interactive Power BI dashboard that analyzes FIFA World Cup 2026 performance up to the semi-finals using Power BI, Power Query, DAX, and data modeling.

![Power BI](https://img.shields.io/badge/Power%20BI-Analytics-F2C811?style=for-the-badge&logo=powerbi&logoColor=black)
![DAX](https://img.shields.io/badge/DAX-Measures-blue?style=for-the-badge)
![Power Query](https://img.shields.io/badge/Power%20Query-Data%20Transformation-green?style=for-the-badge)
![Sports Analytics](https://img.shields.io/badge/Sports-Analytics-red?style=for-the-badge)

---

# 📖 Overview

This project explores the performance of teams and players in the **FIFA World Cup 2026** up to the **Semi-finals**.

The objective was to identify the factors that contributed most to successful teams by combining football statistics with Business Intelligence techniques.

The dashboard was built using **Power BI** and focuses on:

- Team Performance
- Player Impact
- Match Control
- Attacking & Defensive Efficiency
- Semi-finalist Success Factors

---

# 🚀 Features

- Interactive Power BI Dashboard
- Star Schema Data Model
- Power Query Data Cleaning
- Custom DAX Measures
- Team Performance Index
- Team Attack Index
- Team Defense Index
- Match Control Index
- Goal Conversion Analysis
- Player Contribution Analysis
- Executive Dashboard
- Interactive Filters & Slicers

---

# 📊 Dashboard Pages

## 1️⃣ Executive Overview

Provides a tournament-wide summary including:

- Semi-finalists
- Goals per Match
- Performance Index
- Top Performing Teams
- Key Tournament Findings

---

## 2️⃣ Team Performance Analysis

Analyzes what separated semi-finalists from other teams.

Highlights:

- Attack Index
- Defense Index
- Match Control
- Scatter Analysis
- Team Comparison
- Performance Distribution

---

## 3️⃣ Player Impact Analysis

Evaluates individual player contributions across:

- Goal Contribution
- Defensive Contribution
- Goalkeeper Performance
- Position-based Analysis

---

## 4️⃣ Semi-finalist Success Profile

Identifies the defining characteristics of successful teams through:

- Performance Gap Analysis
- Success Factors
- Trade-off Analysis
- Executive Insights

---

# 📈 Key Insights

- Semi-finalists consistently outperformed other teams in Match Control and Possession.

- Attacking efficiency proved to be a stronger differentiator than defensive statistics.

- Elite attacking players had the highest impact on overall team performance.

- Defensive contributions were more evenly distributed among players.

- Controlling possession translated into better goal conversion and attacking output.

